 :tx/rationale "UNSOUNDNESS-LEDGER-12: Schema migration has no backward-incompatible change guard. schema.rs (4,864 LOC) supports schema evolution via transaction — adding new attributes to a running store. But there is no guard for backward-incompatible changes: (1) Changing an attribute's value type (e.g., Long to String) after data exists. Existing datoms now violate the schema. (2) Changing cardinality from Many to One. Existing multi-valued datoms are invalid. (3) Changing resolution mode from Multi to LWW. Existing multi-valued conflicts are not resolved. The schema is rebuilt from datoms (Schema::from_datoms), so the LATEST schema assertion wins via LWW. But the existing datoms that were valid under the old schema are not retroactively validated or migrated. The fix is: schema_validate_datoms(store, schema) that checks ALL datoms against the current schema, not just new ones. Run this after any schema-affecting transaction. Report violations as CoherenceViolation. This is Stage 1 work but the gap should be tracked."
